SOFA Attribution
================================================================================

astrogo's internal/gofaext package uses routines and computations derived
from the github.com/hebl/gofa module (https://github.com/hebl/gofa), which is
itself a Go port of routines from the International Astronomical Union's
"Standards Of Fundamental Astronomy" (SOFA) software (http://www.iausofa.org),
based on SOFA version 19 (2023-10-11 release).

Per the terms of the SOFA Software License:

  (a) This derived work (astrogo) uses routines and computations derived by
      its authors from software provided by SOFA under license, and does not
      itself constitute software provided by and/or endorsed by SOFA.

  (b) astrogo's internal/gofaext package (internal/gofaext/gofaext.go) wraps
      gofa's SOFA-derived routines (e.g. Apco13, Atciq, Atioq, Gst06a, C2t06a,
      Nut06a, Obl06, Pnm06a, Ee06a, Epv00, Moon98, Plan94, Dat, Refco) with
      thin adapters that translate astrogo's own value types (angles in
      radians, two-part Julian dates, etc.) into the argument shapes those
      routines expect. See internal/gofaext/doc.go for details of the
      relationship between astrogo and the underlying gofa/SOFA algorithms.

  (c) No routine name in astrogo or gofaext carries the "iau" or "sofa"
      prefix (or a trivial modification thereof).

  (d) The origin of the SOFA-derived components is cited above and in
      internal/gofaext/doc.go; the original SOFA copyright and license text
      is reproduced in full at:
      https://github.com/hebl/gofa/blob/master/sofa_copyr.txt

